library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)
library(readr)
library(dplyr)
avatar <- readr::read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2020/2020-08-11/avatar.csv')
Parsed with column specification:
cols(
  id = col_double(),
  book = col_character(),
  book_num = col_double(),
  chapter = col_character(),
  chapter_num = col_double(),
  character = col_character(),
  full_text = col_character(),
  character_words = col_character(),
  writer = col_character(),
  director = col_character(),
  imdb_rating = col_double()
)
avatar
# unique(avatar$character)
# filter for main protagonists 
main <- list("Aang","Zuko","Katara","Toph","Sokka","Azula","Iroh")
df <- filter(avatar, character %in% main)
ggplot(data = df, mapping = aes(x = chapter, fill = character))+
  geom_bar(position = "fill")+
  coord_flip()
